---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Resume"
	description="The short version."
	pubDate={new Date('July 11 2026')}
>
	<h2>Jonah Weber</h2>
	<p>Bothell, WA · <a href="https://github.com/docrickman">github.com/docrickman</a></p>

	<h3>TerraPower · IT support, Tier 2</h3>
	<p>
		IT for a nuclear energy R&amp;D company operating in a compliance-heavy government-cloud
		environment. Functionally the senior technical member of the team, with no Tier 3 above.
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Active Directory and M365 administration: account lifecycle, security groups, licensing,
			auditing via Purview, Intune, and the Azure security dashboard.
		</li>
		<li>
			Took the team's PowerShell from ad-hoc one-offs to production tooling: input validation,
			dry-run modes, structured logging, error discrimination. Introduced version control and
			change review where neither existed.
		</li>
		<li>
			Lab IT support: LabVIEW experiment rigs, NI cRIO controllers, Siemens-based systems,
			scientific instruments, air-gapped machines, 24/7 uptime constraints. Ran a Purdue-model
			classification and gap analysis of lab assets.
		</li>
		<li>
			Documentation and process design: KB authorship, a Jira-based documentation
			change-management workflow, technician training paths, and a Git onboarding guide
			written for readers with zero programming background.
		</li>
		<li>Mentor one Tier 1 technician directly; wrote the training path to scale past one.</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Skills</h3>
	<p>If it's listed, I've used it on real work with real consequences. No stars, no bars.</p>

	<h4>Enterprise IT</h4>
	<div class="chips">
		<span class="chip">Active Directory</span>
		<span class="chip">Microsoft 365</span>
		<span class="chip">Intune</span>
		<span class="chip">Azure Purview</span>
		<span class="chip">ConfigMgr</span>
		<span class="chip">GCC High operations</span>
	</div>

	<h4>Scripting and code</h4>
	<div class="chips">
		<span class="chip">PowerShell</span>
		<span class="chip">Python</span>
		<span class="chip">Node.js</span>
		<span class="chip">C#</span>
		<span class="chip">React</span>
		<span class="chip">Lua (Kahlua)</span>
		<span class="chip">Git &amp; GitHub Actions</span>
	</div>

	<h4>Lab and OT</h4>
	<div class="chips">
		<span class="chip">LabVIEW environments</span>
		<span class="chip">NI cRIO</span>
		<span class="chip">OPC UA</span>
		<span class="chip">Siemens-based systems</span>
		<span class="chip">Air-gapped operations</span>
		<span class="chip">Purdue model (PERA)</span>
	</div>

	<h4>Process and writing</h4>
	<div class="chips">
		<span class="chip">Technical documentation</span>
		<span class="chip">KB design</span>
		<span class="chip">Jira/Confluence workflow design</span>
		<span class="chip">Training paths</span>
		<span class="chip">Mentorship</span>
	</div>

	<h4>AI tooling</h4>
	<div class="chips">
		<span class="chip">AI-assisted development</span>
		<span class="chip">Agent skill authoring</span>
		<span class="chip">MCP integrations</span>
	</div>

	<h3>Direction</h3>
	<p>
		OT/IT convergence: the industrial and lab-systems side of IT. Working toward GICSP.
	</p>

	<h3>Elsewhere</h3>
	<p>
		The <a href="/projects">projects</a> and <a href="/notes">write-ups</a> on this site are
		the portfolio; this page is just the frame around them.
	</p>
</Layout>

<style>
	h4 {
		font-size: 1.05em;
		margin: 1.25em 0 0.5em 0;
		color: var(--accent-2);
	}
	.chips {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.5em;
	}
	.chip {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 0.15em 0.7em;
		font-size: 0.82em;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
		background: var(--surface);
		border: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
		border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
		border-radius: 6px;
	}
</style>
